-----------------------<br>
I just came here as a level 27 mage and they are 00ber XP.  This place is NEVER camped so you have the whole place to yourself.<br>
<br>
There are 3 sisters that can be pulled individually, the one standing on the dock, the one by the tree, and Antinimie (the one standing by the shore).<br>
<br>
The other 7 spawns are inside the buildings and you have to pull 2 - 3 at ONCE.  You could pull the duo with malise once you hit level 29, until then, I suggest a necro partner.<br>
<br>
The single pulls almost ALWAYS 9 outta 10 drop purity belts which go for 1 - 2 plat. <br>
<br>
The sisters inside the buildings drop SWORDS that sell 9 - 10 plat guaranteed. They always drop em too.<br>
<br>
Respawn is about 6 minutes on each sister.  DO NOT USE EARTH PET while huntin the sisters.  They run around 1/5 hp and you dont want them double attacking ur pet even more for 52 a hit.  I HIGHLY recommend Air or Water.<br>
<br>
This should be constant pulls.  I got 100 pp in one hour from camping these.  If you get too bored pull the occasional dwarf.<br>
<br>
LAKE OF ILL OMEN (level 24 - 34)<br>
--------------------------------<br>
I love Lake of Ill Omen sarnak fort at this level.  The sarnaks have little hp and hit fast, for moderate damage.   Just camp around the ridge, or if the main fort is too camped go next to the backdoor, where you can single pull wanderers non stop to a safe spot (right where the rock and grass merge).  If you get too bored, there are usually enough classes LFG for you to form your own, and you could take the Chancellor room, which is UBER XP, (1 yellow bub every 20 - 30 minutes).  You need the perfect group that knows what they are doing though.<br>
<br>
BRUTES IN WARSILK WOODS (level 24 - 34)<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
Coming in from OT, you just follow the left wall till u see Dalnir ruins.  Go down the passageway some (the one that leads to the Dalnir zone) and you should see Gorging brutes.  These guys have no aggro range so u could poke their toes and they won't care.  You could sit beneath their tummy and they don't care.  This is a THREE spawn, and each spawn takes about 18 minutes to refresh.  You kill one (the others wont assist) and med to full, kill another one, med to full.  By the time your done killing the last one, the first one should spawn...<br>
<br>
BANDITS IN WARSILK WOODS (level 18 - level 24)<br>
-------------------------------------------------<br>
A monk is required for this strategy, because they can FD pull.  From OT zone turn RIGHT until you see water.  Follow the river left (it should be going to lower elevations) till u see a bandit camp on the left of the river.  This is often called the &quot;pariah and manslayer camp&quot; because thats all thats spawns here.  Don't get too close to the camp or else the iksars will aggro through the walls.  There are 3 that spawn on one side, and 3 that spawn on the other side.  I suggest moving away from the river to the isolate building (empty) near the other 3 spawn.  This is a safe place and there are NO WANDERERS here.  Proceed to FD pull (all you need is a monk partner, tons of bandages, and mend (right when it refreshes monk should push it).  You will pull 3, but when monk FD's they wander in a circle and the monk should be able to pick off the last one.  If you guys get too bored, you could pull the iksars from the other side.<br>
<br>
A HINT FOR NOOBIES <br>
--------------------<br>
Run to the Field of Bone to level as a newbie.  LOIO has too many high level wanderers.  Field of bone pit is the FASTEST possible way you can get from 1 - 16.<br>
