<br>
Several changes to this area have been made tho.   <br>
<br>
1.  The Brutes now have a small aggro radius and will assist each other if the one being killed get too close to another one.  This is not really problem, a heal or two and you can get a decent pet to tank 2 at one time.  All you have to do is be careful and kill them when they start walking and you will be fine with single pulls.<br>
<br>
2.  I am now level 30.   I am seeing Light Blue spawns now.  I do not think that I will stay much longer.  The xp is ok if you are killing blues, but the L Blues are just too weak to deal with in terms of xp.<br>
<br>
3.  There are bug issues in this place to watch out for.  As long as you kill the brutes before they get near the wall you are fine.  Otherwise they will go IN TO THE WALL and take YOUR PET with them.  That really sucks!  If that happens, just watch for the you gain xp to pop up and go invis and then recast yourself a new pet.  Low level hill giants and goblins will &quot;fall&quot; into the walls from above every now and again and cause you the same problems, just zone to Dalnir and then back in and get a new pet.<br>
<br>
4.  There are two places you can camp here, a two spawn and a three spawn.  I did both as a circle from 24 to now at 30.  All the spawns are now on about a 12 minute timer.  I usually med to about half and then &quot;go-a-kill'in&quot;.  <br>
<br>
The hardest I was ever hit was for 60.  They are really easy if you are careful and I highly recommend this place for 22 to 30.  I found that the DS on the fire pet was just too sweet and that is the one I used the most.  I never needed to use a heal unless a runner got aggro from another.  <br>
<br>
